literals: 'Cannot use an EBS alias as `environmentEndpoint`. You must find your EBS environment endpoint via the AWS console. See the Elastic Beanstalk developer guide: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/elasticbeanstalk/latest/dg/customdomains.html'
Elastic Beanstalk environment target is not supported for the "${region}" region.
docstrings:
* Use an Elastic Beanstalk environment URL as an alias record target.
 * E.g. mysampleenvironment.xyz.us-east-1.elasticbeanstalk.com
 *
 * Only supports Elastic Beanstalk environments created after 2016 that have a regional endpoint.
